<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Extend existing words:</span> If PLAY is on the board, adding ABLE to make PLAYABLE scores all 8 letters plus any premium squares the extension crosses. Look for verbs ending near the board edge.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Save your B tile:</span> B is worth 3 points and relatively scarce (only 2 in the bag). If you have A, L, E tiles already, hold the B for an -ABLE extension rather than using it in a low-scoring play.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Bingo factory:</span> -ABLE creates 7+ letter words from common 3-4 letter roots. Keep ABLE tiles together and look for short roots on the board: SUIT+ABLE, WORK+ABLE, BREAK+ABLE.</p>
  </div>
</div>

